Install:

./configure
make
su -c make install


Uninstall:

su -c make uninstall

Suse users may have trouble with configure and undefined macro's.  The fix
that was offered by vbdoor on KDE-Look.org was to copy the admin from 
/opt/kde3/share/apps/kdelibs/admin over kdesktop_menu-VERSION/admin -- then
run make -f admin/Makefile.common dist -- and finally rerun configure.
